The National Universities Commission (NUC), has granted full accreditation to five undergraduate academic programmes in the Ladoke Akintola University of Technology (LAUTECH), Ogbomoso, to last for a period of five years. The Commission in a letter dated April 14, 2022, and signed on behalf of its Executive Secretary by the organizationâ€™s Director of Accreditation, Dr Maryam Sali, listed the programmes to include: Fine and Applied Arts, Agricultural Engineering, Chemical Engineering as well as Pure and Applied Physics and Statistics. The letter explained that the accreditation granted to the programmes (which are not new), is consequent upon the accreditation exercise carried out in LAUTECH between October and November 2021.